# Public repo: DEFAULT-DENY. Ignore everything, then explicitly allow only the
# hand-authored config files. This way a stray secret, a Klipper SAVE_CONFIG
# backup, a third-party symlinked file, or any new/unknown file can NEVER be
# pushed by the automated backup.
*

# --- allow the meta files ---
!.gitignore
!README.md
!LICENSE

# --- allow the authored Klipper / Moonraker / peripheral configs ---
!printer.cfg
!moonraker.conf
!crowsnest.conf
!timelapse.cfg

# Explicitly-excluded-by-design (already covered by the '*' default-deny, listed
# here as documentation of WHY they must never be tracked):
#   moonraker-obico.cfg        -> contains a private auth_token (SECRET)
#   printer-*.cfg              -> Klipper SAVE_CONFIG auto-backups
#   mainsail.cfg               -> third-party symlink (regenerated on install)
#   moonraker_obico_macros.cfg -> third-party symlink
#   *.backup / .*.bkp          -> editor/moonraker backups
